Murumuru Butter — a fun name but a seriously good moisturizer 💖 

Our partner farming communities handpick fallen murumuru nuts from Bellem, a small village at the south of the Amazon River, and hand-crush them to take out fresh murumuru butter for you. This ethically-sourced ingredient is then loaded into our bottles without additional chemicals such as parabens, dyes or mineral oil.

It’s called liquid gold for a reason 💛 

Ethically sourced from Morocco, we ensure our argan oil is organic & of the finest quality to give you the best care. Local Moroccan women handpick argan nuts, crush them & carefully extract this rich, moisturizing oil. 

Sustainable, fair-trade & pure, we believe in beauty that gives love to you, to them & the planet! ✨

#lovebeautyandplanet #arganoil #moroccanarganoil #ethicallysourced #ethicalsourcing #sustainablebeauty #naturalingredients

Hair products that work wonders = 💜 But hair products that work wonders AND smell great = 💜💜💜💜 
 
To make your hair care routine smell amazing, we ethically source this essential oil from France using a ‘prefane’ technique to ensure the highest quality fragrance. 

Our fragrance partner, Givaudan, works with a cooperative of 100 local farmers that painstakingly handpick these lavender sprigs & extract an organic artisanal blend that leaves behind a deliciously soothing scent! 💆🏻‍♀️
